  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and regulations to combat money laundering:\n\n1. Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- Sets global standards for preventing money laundering\n- Develops recommendations for financial institutions and governments\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention against Corruption\n\n3. International Monetary Fund (IMF) Guidelines\n- Provides recommendations for preventing financial crimes\n\n4. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Sets international banking standards\n\n5. Specific Regional Regulations\n- European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Bank Secrecy Act in the United States\n\nMost countries have national laws that implement these international standards, requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThese laws aim to detect and prevent illegal financial activities, track the origins of funds, and disrupt criminal enterprises.",
